Statements:
[
    "MGS is responsible for managing metadata in the Lustre file system.",
    "MGS handles the creation and mounting of the file system using mkfs.lustre and mount.lustre commands.",
    "MGS provides configuration information for the file system, which clients use to access it correctly.",
    "MGS coordinates HSM operations involving data migration requests.",
    "MGS supports network management functions including LNet startup/shutdown and InfiniBand load balancing.",
    "MGS can be configured in high availability mode with multiple mgsnode values for reliability.",
    "MGS allows setting the MDT to read-only mode via specific parameters."
] 

