Statements:
[
    "Lustre 文件系统的核心组件包括 MGS、MDS、MDT、OSS 和 OST.",
    "These components work together to achieve a high-performance and scalable distributed file system.",
    "1. MGS (管理服务器) stores configuration information for all Lustre file systems in the cluster and provides this information to other components.",
    "2. Each Lustre target contacts MGS to get information.",
    "3. MGS can co-locate with MDS and share storage space.",
    "4. MDS makes metadata stored on one or multiple MDTs available for clients.",
    "5. Each MDS manages names and directories in the file system.",
    "6. Each MDS provides network request handling for one or more local MDTs.",
    "7. MDT stores metadata on attached storage under the control of an MDS.",
    "8. Metadata includes things like filenames, directories, permissions, and file layout.",
    "9. Although shared storage targets have MDT that can be used by multiple MDS, only one MDS can access it at a time.",
    "10. OSS provides I/O services for OSTs.",
    "11. Each OST stores file data.",
    "12. OSS works with multiple OSTs to improve storage performance and capacity.",
    "13. OST is the actual device that stores file data.",
    "14. Each OST stores a part of each file.",
    "15. Clients perform read-write operations based on layout information provided by MDS.",
    "16. Data can be evenly distributed among OSTs, matching network bandwidth."
] 

